The paper deals with the problem of ranking items in web applications, which is a common problem in machine learning and information retrieval. The use of bandit algorithms and the focus on sequential ranking suggest that the paper belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). However, the problem also involves user behavior and interaction with the interface, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of algorithms to optimize the ranking of items also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of recommending items based on user feedback, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS).
